REQUEST: REMOVE JUNK/TRASH AND COMMERCIAL VEHICLES FROM VACANT LOT REFERENCED BELOW.  VACANT LOT LOCATION AND ISSUES - FACING HOUSE ADDRESS: 1060 N 35TH ST, BATON ROUGE, LA 70802   -- ISSUE:  BOTH VACANT LOTS LEFT OF HOUSE ADDRESS ABOVE HAS COMMERCIAL VEHICLES AND JUNK THROUGHOUT VACANT LOTS.      --- VACANT LOT #1:             PARCEL ID:  209597           LOT:  21           BLOCK:  4      --- VACANT LOT #2:           PARCEL ID:  209589           LOT:  22           BLOCK:  4 - SUBDIVISION: EDEN PARK  ADDITIONAL ISSUES: - OWNER LEFT MULTIPLE COMMERCIAL VEHICLES (SEMI TRUCKS) ON VACANT LOT VIOLATING LOUISIANA ORDINANCE - THE PRESENCE OF A COMMERCIAL VEHICLES (E.G. SEMI-TRUCK, DUMP TRUCK, ETC.) PARKED IN A RESIDENTIAL AREA CAN CAUSE SIGNIFICANT ISSUES FOR RESIDENTS AND IS MORE THAN JUST A NUISANCE. HERE’S WHY:  1. SAFETY FIRST: SEMI-TRUCKS/DUMP TRUCKS ARE MASSIVE, OFTEN WEIGHING UP TO 80,000 POUNDS WHEN FULLY LOADED. THAT MAKES THEM A POTENTIAL HAZARD IN NEIGHBORHOODS WHERE KIDS PLAY, CYCLISTS RIDE, AND CARS TRAVEL. A PARKED SEMI OR DUMP TRUCK CAN BLOCK VISIBILITY, NARROW STREETS, OR EVEN OBSTRUCT EMERGENCY VEHICLES.  2. NOISE POLLUTION: TRUCKS ARE LOUD FOR MANY REASONS. THE ENGINES, ESPECIALLY THOSE USING DIESEL, MAKE A TON OF NOISE FROM BURNING FUEL AND THE EXHAUST SYSTEM. BIG TIRES ROLLING ON THE ROAD ALSO CREATE NOISE, WHICH GETS LOUDER AS THE TRUCK GOES FASTER OR TIRES WEAR DOWN. THE WAY TRUCKS ARE DESIGNED TO CUT THROUGH THE AIR, EVEN THOUGH IT SAVES FUEL, CAN ALSO MAKE THEM NOISY AT HIGH SPEEDS. PLUS, OTHER PARTS LIKE BRAKES, SUSPENSION, AND TRANSMISSION ADD TO THE NOISE ISSUE.  3. TRAFFIC FLOW PROBLEMS: A SEMI-TRUCK OR DUMP TRUCK TAKES UP WAY MORE SPACE THAN A CAR. PARK ONE IN A RESIDENTIAL AREA, AND SUDDENLY DRIVEWAYS ARE BLOCKED, SIDEWALKS ARE INACCESSIBLE, OR ENTIRE LANES OF TRAFFIC CEASE MOVING.  4. AESTHETICS MATTER: MANY NEIGHBORHOODS HAVE A CERTAIN CHARM OR CHARACTER, AND A COMMERCIAL VEHICLE LIKE A SEMI-TRUCK OR DUMP TRUCK DOESN’T ALWAYS FIT THE VIBE.  5. ENVIRONMENTAL CONCERNS: DIESEL EMISSIONS FROM IDLING TRUCKS CONTRIBUTE TO AIR POLLUTION, WHICH IS ESPECIALLY PROBLEMATIC IN DENSELY POPULATED AREAS LIKE THROUGHOUT BATON ROUGE, LA.  CONTACT: - VERONICA E. SMITH - XXX-XXX-XXXX - LAGRITS21@YAHOO.COM AND LAGRITS21@OUTLOOK.COM

comments: 1. INCIDENT INFORMATION •	ADDRESS: 1524 SHERWOOD FOREST BLVD, BATON ROUGE, LOUISIANA •	VIOLATION TYPE: CODE VIOLATION DUE TO HAZARDOUS DEBRIS AND POTENTIAL SOIL CONTAMINATION FOLLOWING A FIRE  2. DESCRIPTION OF INCIDENT •	FIRE EVENT: O	A HOUSE ON THE PROPERTY RECENTLY CAUGHT ON FIRE. •	DEBRIS ISSUE: O	A PILE OF DEBRIS REMAINS IN THE FRONT YARD NEAR THE CURB. O	CONCERNS INCLUDE POSSIBLE CONTAMINATION OF THE SOIL BY TOXIC SUBSTANCES FROM THE FIRE AND THE PHYSICAL HAZARD THE DEBRIS POSES.  3. OBSERVATIONS & SAFETY CONCERNS •	ENVIRONMENTAL HAZARD: O	DEBRIS MAY CONTAIN TOXIC CHEMICALS, HEAVY METALS, OR OTHER CONTAMINANTS THAT COULD LEACH INTO THE SOIL. •	PUBLIC SAFETY RISKS: O	THE DEBRIS PILE CREATES TRIPPING HAZARDS AND MIGHT CONTRIBUTE TO A POTENTIAL RE-IGNITION RISK IF ANY MATERIALS REMAIN SMOLDERING. •	CODE NON-COMPLIANCE: O	THE CURRENT CONDITION MAY VIOLATE LOCAL REGULATIONS REGARDING PROPERTY MAINTENANCE AND ENVIRONMENTAL SAFETY.  4. ON-SITE RESOURCES & ADDITIONAL OBSERVATIONS •	AVAILABLE DUMPSTER: O	AN ON-SITE DUMPSTER IS AVAILABLE; REQUEST ASSESSMENT ON WHETHER THE DEBRIS CAN BE SAFELY RELOCATED INSIDE THE DUMPSTER .  ENVIRONMENTAL CONCERNS •	SOIL CONTAMINATION: O	CHEMICAL RESIDUES: BURNING MATERIALS CAN RELEASE TOXIC CHEMICALS SUCH AS POLYCYCLIC AROMATIC HYDROCARBONS (PAHS), DIOXINS, AND OTHER HAZARDOUS COMPOUNDS THAT MAY SEEP INTO THE SOIL. O	HEAVY METALS: MATERIALS FROM THE FIRE, INCLUDING TREATED WOOD, PLASTICS, OR INSULATION, CAN RELEASE HEAVY METALS LIKE LEAD OR ARSENIC, POSING LONG-TERM RISKS TO SOIL HEALTH AND LOCAL ECOSYSTEMS. •	WATER QUALITY IMPACT: O	LEACHATE RISK: CONTAMINANTS IN THE DEBRIS MAY LEACH INTO THE GROUNDWATER OR NEARBY SURFACE WATER, POTENTIALLY AFFECTING LOCAL WATER SUPPLIES AND AQUATIC LIFE. O	RUNOFF ISSUES: DURING RAIN EVENTS, CONTAMINANTS CAN BE WASHED OFF THE DEBRIS PILE AND SPREAD TO SURROUNDING AREAS, COMPOUNDING THE ENVIRONMENTAL HAZARD. •	AIR QUALITY CONCERNS: O	RESIDUAL PARTICULATES: EVEN AFTER THE FIRE, SMALL PARTICLES OR RESIDUAL SMOKE PARTICLES MAY REMAIN, AFFECTING AIR QUALITY IN THE IMMEDIATE VICINITY. O	CHEMICAL OFF-GASSING: CERTAIN MATERIALS MAY CONTINUE TO OFF-GAS HARMFUL CHEMICALS OVER TIME, CONTRIBUTING TO DEGRADED LOCAL AIR QUALITY.   SAFETY CONCERNS •	PHYSICAL HAZARDS: O	TRIPPING AND FALLING RISKS: THE DISORGANIZED PILE OF DEBRIS CREATES UNEVEN SURFACES, LEADING TO POTENTIAL TRIPPING HAZARDS FOR PEDESTRIANS, CHILDREN, AND THE ELDERLY. O	OBSTRUCTION OF VISIBILITY: DEBRIS LOCATED NEAR THE CURB CAN OBSTRUCT SIGHTLINES FOR BOTH DRIVERS AND PEDESTRIANS, INCREASING THE RISK OF ACCIDENTS. •	FIRE AND RE-IGNITION RISK: O	SMOLDERING MATERIALS: IF ANY DEBRIS REMAINS HOT OR SMOLDERING, THERE IS A RISK OF RE-IGNITION, POSING AN ONGOING FIRE HAZARD. O	UNCONTROLLED BURNING: UNATTENDED DEBRIS THAT CONTAINS FLAMMABLE MATERIALS MAY POSE A FIRE THREAT, ESPECIALLY IN DRY OR WINDY CONDITIONS. •	HEALTH AND SAFETY OF RESIDENTS: O	DIRECT EXPOSURE TO TOXINS: RESIDENTS MAY BE DIRECTLY EXPOSED TO TOXIC SUBSTANCES THROUGH CONTACT WITH CONTAMINATED SOIL OR INHALATION OF OFF-GASSING CHEMICALS, LEADING TO BOTH ACUTE AND CHRONIC HEALTH ISSUES. O	LONG-TERM EXPOSURE RISKS: PROLONGED EXPOSURE TO THE ENVIRONMENTAL CONTAMINANTS CAN INCREASE THE RISK OF RESPIRATORY ISSUES, SKIN IRRITATION, OR OTHER HEALTH PROBLEMS.

TO THE CITY OF BATON ROUGE:   GINGER FORD, RESIDING AT 639 CAMELLIA STREET, BATON ROUGE, 70806 IS IN VIOLATION OF CHAPTER 9 PG 27 9.3.7   MS GINGER FORD HAS TAKEN UPON HERSELF TO PLANT UNWANTED GARDENS BEDS  THROUGHOUT THE GARDEN DISTRICT & ALONG PARK BLVD.   1.	 THE UNSIGHTLY GARDENS ARE INSTALLED ON BATON ROUGE CITY PROPERTY AT EACH CROSS ROAD ON CAMELLIA STREET AND PARK BLVD, ADJACENT TO HOMES WITHOUT HOMEOWNER’S PERMISSION .  2.	THE GARDENS ARE NOT CONSISTENTLY MAINTAINED FROM MARCH TO NOVEMBER & BECOME UNRULY.  3.	THE UNRULY GARDENS VISUALLY IMPAIR DRIVER’S VISION WHEN AT STOP SIGNS TRYING TO CROSS OVER CAMELLIA WHICH IS MAIN THOROUGHFARE IN THE GARDEN DISTRICT. 4.	OVER THE LAST THREE YEARS 2.5’ TO  3’ HIGH CONCRETE STATUES HAVE BEEN ADDED AND GLASS GLOBES FOR “DECORATION” ON EACH CORNER ALONG CAMELLIA STREET . THESE CONCRETE STATUES BLOCK FIRE HYDRANTS AND ARE A DANGER TO VEHICLES. IF A VEHICLE WERE TO ACCIDENTALLY SWERVE AND HIT A CONCRETE STATUE (THAT IS ON BR CITY PROPERTY) THE VEHICLE WOULD BE SEVERELY DAMAGED AND THE PASSENGERS IN THE CAR.  5.	DEBRIS AND DANGEROUS GARDEN TOOLS/BRICKS ARE REGULARLY LEFT ON THE SIDEWALKS CAUSING PEDESTRIANS IN WHEELCHAIRS TO HAVE TO GO ON THE STREET AND BACK UP ON THE SIDEWALK TO NAVIGATE AROUND THE SHARP TOOLS/ AND BRICKS. 6.	WHEN THE PLANTS ARE WATERED GINGER WILL DRIVE HER VEHICLE ALONG CAMELLIA FREQUENTLY STOPPING AT EACH CORNER CAUSING TRAFFIC ISSUES. MS FORD WILL EITHER HOOK HER HOSE UP TO A RESIDENTIAL WATER SPOUT (WITHOUT PERMISSION FROM THE HOMEOWNER) AND USE THE HOMEOWNER’S SERVICES. OR SHE WILL FERRY WATER FROM THE TRUNK OF HER VEHICLE TO THE PLANTS, REGULARLY  STOPPING IN THE MIDDLE OF THE STREET CAUSING TRAFFIC ISSUES.  7.	LAST SPRING I PERSONALLY WITNESSED AN AMBULANCE TRYING TO GET TO A RESIDENT IN CRITICAL NEED. THE AMBULANCE HAD TO STOP, REVERSE AND DRIVE DOWN A DIFFERENT STREET TO GET TO THE PATIENT BECAUSE MS FORD’S CAR WAS BLOCKING CAMELLIA STREET WHILE SHE WAS INSTALLING PLANTS ON CITY PROPERTY.  LAST SPRING MS FORD STARTED EXPANDING HER “GARDENS” AND  STAKED DOWN LARGE BLUE TARPS ON THE MEDIAN ON PARK BLVD IN PREPARATION FOR CREATING THE SAME HAZARDOUS GARDENS AS ON CAMELLIA STREET.   PLEASE SEE PICTURES TO FOLLOW SHOWING SUNFLOWERS THAT HAVE GOTTEN SO TALL THAT MS FORD USES ROPE TO TIE THE PLANTS TO CITY STOP SIGNS SO THE PLANTS DO NOT FALL OVER.  ALSO INCLUDED IS A PICTIRE OF A 3’ TALL CONCRETE BIRD BATH BLOCKING A CITY FIRE HYDRANT.   GINGER FORD DOES NOT HAVE A PERMIT TO DO THIS. HOMEOWNERS DO NOT WANT MS GINGER TO CONTINUE THESE CARELESS ACTIONS AND WANT A STOP THESE HAZARDOUS UNSIGHTLY PLANT BEDS.  THEY ARE A PUBLIC NUISANCE.  THEY ARE DANGEROUS. THEY ARE ON CITY PROPERTY WITHOUT PERMISSION.  THIS HAS BEEN GOING ON FOR OVER 5 YEARS AND IS OUT OF HAND.
